= Introduction

Computer vision algorithms have long played a significant role in the analysis of medical images, supporting clinical decision-making in use cases such as MRI or CT images. In particular, computer vision techniques applied to X-ray imaging can serve as an effective preliminary tool for the early detection and diagnosis of diseases with a visual interpretation. VinBigData leveraged the growing interest in this field by organizing a competition in 2021 and releasing a carefully curated and extensively annotated dataset of chest X-ray anomalies @nguyen2020vindrcxr.

Building on recent advances addressing this challenging computer vision problem, our work aims to leverage and adapt effective existing baseline approaches while further developing advanced methods based on state-of-the-art detection models scaling correctly through native bounding-box ensembles.
